      "content": "it's not just a feeling though. i've been recording it with my phone when it's quiet and if you look at the waveform, it's not a steady sine wave. it's modulated. there's this specific drop in frequency every 4.2 seconds that feels like it's trying to sync up with a heartbeat. wouldn't that kind of frequency modulation be a way to mess with people's nervous systems without them even realizing it?",
